      "content": "The \"pragmatic decision\" angle is okay, but I'm worried. If a reporter brings up the specific points the candidate used to attack the bill—like the impact on middle-class families—and asks why those concerns suddenly don't matter anymore, how do we answer that without it looking like a total lie? I don't want them looking like they just folded to party leadership.",
